Description: Page from photograph album containing views of Egypt and the Middle East:six photographs depicting the excavations of Sir Leonard Woolley in progress at Ur. One picture of Woolley and his wife Katherine at the site and one of Woolley holding a gold bull's head from an ancient lyre recently excavated in the "Royal Cemetery" at the site.
Producer name: Photographed by: Rev William Percy Hughes
Associated names: Portrait of: Rev William Percy Hughes
